0Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDetermining%20the%20exact%20price%20of%20a%20luxury%20item%2C%20whether%20it's%20a%20handbag%20or%20a%20white%20tee%2C%20is%20more%20of%20an%20art%20than%20a%20science.%20Unlike%20with%20mass%20retailers%20like%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzara-inditex-pandora-thrive-amid-luxury-downturn-aspirational-consumer-trends-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGap%20or%20Zara%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it's%20less%20about%20the%20price%20of%20the%20materials%20and%20production%20and%20more%20about%20perception.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNobody%20needs%20a%20%24500%20T-shirt%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicole%20Marra%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20brand%20consultancy%20Fixer%20Advisory%20Group%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20selling%20a%20dream.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2232d72bc2-9510-4901-b3b9-7f44fa6aa18e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'All%20cotton%20T-shirts%20are%20not%20created%20equal'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20mere%20mortals%20have%20not%20seen%20a%20T-shirt%20from%20The%20Row%20up%20close%2C%20felt%20the%20cotton%2C%20or%20investigated%20the%20stitching.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20did%2C%20chances%20are%20you'd%20be%20a%20little%20impressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20cotton%20T-shirts%20are%20not%20created%20equal%2C%26quot%3B%20Marra%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20for%20creating%20a%20better%20one%20is%20more%20expensive%20at%20every%20step%2C%20starting%20with%20the%20design.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222586%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Row%20website%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690e5e83513c94655a3ddf6b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221298%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20white%20T-shirt%20is%20a%20closet%20staple.%20This%20one%20just%20costs%20%24520.%3Cp%3EScreenshot%20of%20TheRow.com%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20achieve%20The%20Tori's%20shrunken%20fit%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bone%20that's%20more%20luxe%20and%20hangs%20just%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20Marra%20said%20%E2%80%94%20The%20Row%20may%20have%20its%20(expensive)%20designer%20create%20and%20order%20a%20dozen%20(expensive)%20samples%2C%20each%20of%20which%20has%20to%20be%20sourced%20and%20produced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20like%20with%20any%20item%20of%20clothing%2C%20there%20are%20materials%20and%20manufacturing%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20the%20Tori%20T-shirt%2C%20that%20means%20expensive%2C%20extra-soft%20cotton%20and%20manufacturing%20in%20Italy%2C%20where%20labor%20costs%20more%20than%20in%20countries%20like%20China%20or%20Bangladesh%2C%20which%20produce%20your%20run-of-the-mill%20white%20shirt.%20Luxury%20clothing%20in%20Italy%20is%20made%20in%20small%20batches%20and%20hand-finished%20using%20the%20finest%20fabrics%2C%20Marra%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20see%20the%20craftsmanship%20that%20goes%20into%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20refinement%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20the%20brand's%20marketing%20and%20retail%20experience%20%E2%80%94%20is%20baked%20into%20the%20cost.%20The%20Row's%20boutiques%20are%20located%20on%20ritzy%20stretches%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flabor-day-weekend-hamptons-takeaways-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENew%20York's%20Amagansett%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Upper%20East%20Side%20with%20top-of-the-line%20salespeople.%20And%2C%20while%20The%20Row%20doesn't%20have%20flashy%20magazine%20ads%20or%20celebrity%20billboards%2C%20it%20does%20invest%20in%20fashion%20shows%20in%20Paris%2C%20photo%20shoots%2C%20and%20gifting%20for%20loyal%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20all%20built%20into%20the%20price%20of%20that%20shirt%2C%26quot%3B%20Herzog%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20costs%20mean%20that%20even%20at%20%24520%2C%20the%20margins%20are%20likely%20only%20slightly%20higher%20than%20average%2C%20Shikha%20Jain%2C%20the%20lead%20partner%20for%20consumer%20and%20retail%20at%20advisory%20Simon-Kucher%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20T-shirt%20from%20fast%20fashion%20could%20also%20still%20have%20a%2050%25%20margin%20versus%20a%20high-end%20T-shirt%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20dollar%20value%2C%20that'll%20be%20different.%20So%2050%25%20on%20%2420%20is%20%2410%3B%2050%25%20on%20%24500%20is%20%24250.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220ee13c3d-794e-442c-9000-5382d4c45a5d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20price%20of%20perception%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20materials%20and%20production%20account%20for%20part%20of%20the%20cost%2C%20the%20remainder%20is%20less%20tangible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20brand%20could%20probably%20sell%20its%20%24520%20T-shirt%20for%20%24400%20and%20still%20maintain%20a%20healthy%20profit%20margin%2C%20or%20%24600%20and%20still%20find%20a%20buyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20product%20is%20more%20than%20just%20its%20physical%20attributes%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20in%20luxury%2C%26quot%3B%20Jain%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20just%20talking%20about%20the%20raw%20materials%2C%20the%20labor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223861%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mary-Kate%20and%20Ashley%20Olsen%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690e64757f37aa653f55aabb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222574%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMary-Kate%20and%20Ashley%20Olsen's%20fashion%20line%20is%20known%20for%20its%20quality%20just%20as%20much%20as%20for%20its%20brand%20halo.%3Cp%3ELexie%20Moreland%2FWWD%2FPenske%20Media%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20the%20art%20of%20pricing%20comes%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20merchandising%2C%20product%2C%20and%20finance%20teams%20set%20the%20product's%20final%20price%20based%20on%20brand%20as%20much%20as%20%E2%80%94%20if%20not%20more%20than%20%E2%80%94%20the%20cost%20of%20actually%20making%20the%20goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20brand%20is%20perhaps%20what%20The%20Row%20is%20selling%20above%20all%20else%20%E2%80%94%20and%20its%20brand%20has%20value.%20The%20fashion%20label%20was%20the%20fourth%20hottest%20brand%20of%20the%20third%20quarter%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Lyst%20Index%2C%20which%20measures%20the%20popularity%20of%20luxury%20brands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20%24500%20tee%20from%20The%20Row%20is%20not%20priced%20based%20on%20cotton%20and%20stitching%2C%20but%20on%20meaning%2C%20emotion%2C%20and%20perception%2C%26quot%3B%20Daniel%20Langer%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20luxury%20strategy%20firm%20%C3%89quit%C3%A9%20and%20Luxury%20Professor%20at%20Pepperdine%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompetition%20helps%20shape%20that%20perception.%20Pricing%20can%20be%20a%20crucial%20indicator%20of%20a%20brand's%20position%20within%20the%20luxury%20ecosystem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20one%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquiet-luxury-needs-to-die-luxury-brand-earnings-bofa-analysts-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EThe%20Row's%20competitors%2C%20Khaite%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20say%2C%20were%20to%20sell%20its%20cotton%20tee%20for%20%24300%2C%20customers%20might%20think%20The%20Row's%20is%20a%20rip-off.%20If%20Khaite%20was%20selling%20a%20%24700%20T-shirt%2C%20shoppers%20might%20assume%20it's%20better%20than%20The%20Row's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScarcity%2C%20or%20as%20Herzog%20called%20it%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20brand's%20ability%20to%20create%20a%20FOMO%20on%20a%20product%2C%26quot%3B%20can%20also%20play%20a%20role%20in%20the%20strategy.%20The%20Row's%20%24620%20Ama%20slides%20%E2%80%94%20think%20Adidas%20shower%20shoe%20%E2%80%94%20were%20produced%20in%20a%20limited%20quantity%20this%20summer%20and%20swiftly%20sold%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20is%20still%20a%20real%20finger-to-the-wind%20quality%20to%20the%20exercise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20often%20still%20a%20gut%20feeling%2C%20looking%20left%20and%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20Langer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20again%2C%20to%20the%20luxury%20buyer%2C%20the%20price%20may%20not%20matter%20all%20that%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20can%20afford%20to%20be%20in%20on%20the%20coolest%2C%20most%20beautiful%20fabric%2C%20hottest%20T-shirt%2C%20that's%20going%20to%20look%20perfect%20under%20your%20blazer%2C%26quot%3B%20Marra%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhy%20not%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20to%20put%20it%20in%20some%20perspective%2C%20it's%20a%20lot%20cheaper%20than%20The%20Row's%20other%20T-shirt%20options.%20A%20cashmere%20model%3F%20That%20will%20cost%20you%20%241%2C050.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-the-row-white-cotton-t-shirt-cost-brand-expensive-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1762598881000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690cf5097f37aa653f558be6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-the-row-white-cotton-t-shirt-cost-brand-expensive-2025-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20plain%20white%20T-shirt%20designed%20by%20Mary-Kate%20Olsen%20and%20Ashley%20Olsen%20costs%20more%20than%20some%20iPhones.%20Here's%20how%20it%20became%20so%20expensive.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mberg%40businessinsider.com%20(Madeline%20Berg)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A53%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-the-row-white-cotton-t-shirt-cost-brand-expensive-2025-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22These%20are%20the%20states%20where%20Tesla%20is%20racing%20to%20hit%20Elon%20Musk's%20end-of-year%20Robotaxi%20goal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Tesla%20Robotaxi%20on%20the%20streets%20in%20Austin%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6859750985e81483682c902d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Tesla%20Robotaxi%20on%20the%20streets%20in%20Austin.%20The%20service%20launched%20in%20limited%20form%20on%20June%2022%2C%202025.%3Cp%3EJoel%20Angel%20Juarez%2FREUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETesla%20is%20on%20a%20hiring%20spree%20as%20it%20races%20to%20roll%20out%20robotaxi%20service%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20EV%20maker%20is%20seeking%20regulatory%20approval%20in%20several%20states%20and%20has%20listed%20over%2040%20job%20openings.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EElon%20Musk%20has%20said%20Tesla%20plans%20to%20expand%20robotaxis%20to%20eight%20to%2010%20metro%20areas%20by%20the%20end%20of%202025.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EElon%20Musk%20has%20said%20the%20company's%20value%20hinges%20on%20cracking%20autonomous%20driving%20at%20scale.%20Now%2C%20with%20a%20year-end%20deadline%20to%20operate%20Robotaxis%20in%20up%20to%2010%20cities%2C%20the%20company%20is%20hiring%20across%20the%20country%20to%20make%20it%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20said%20in%20October%20that%20Tesla%20plans%20to%20operate%20the%20program%20in%20eight%20to%2010%20metropolitan%20areas%20by%20the%20end%20of%202025%2C%20with%20a%20total%20of%20more%20than%201%2C000%20vehicles.%20So%20far%2C%20it%20has%20launched%20in%20San%20Francisco%20and%20Austin.%20During%20its%20annual%20shareholder%20meeting%20on%20November%206%2C%20the%20company%20said%20it's%20targeting%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20Phoenix%2C%20Dallas%2C%20Houston%2C%20and%20Miami%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20job%20listings%20paint%20an%20even%20broader%20picture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20early%20November%2C%20Tesla%20had%20more%20than%2040%20Robotaxi-related%20postings%20in%20cities%20like%20Orlando%2C%20Tampa%2C%20and%20Las%20Vegas.%20The%20roles%2C%20which%20range%20from%20support%20to%20management%2C%20appear%20geared%20toward%20supporting%20a%20driverless%20fleet%20by%20cleaning%20the%20vehicles%20and%20overseeing%20logistics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Austin%2C%20Tesla%20is%20hiring%20for%20vehicle%20operators%20and%20specialists%20who%20can%20respond%20to%20%26quot%3Bvehicle%20incidents%20in%20the%20field.%26quot%3B%20Tesla%20already%20employs%20three%20fleet%20support%20specialists%20in%20the%20city%2C%20according%20to%20LinkedIn.%20In%20San%20Francisco%2C%20the%20company%20continues%20to%20hire%20engineers%20for%20its%20Autopilot%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20also%20employs%20test%20drivers%20%E2%80%94%20who%20are%20responsible%20for%20training%20the%20autonomous%20software%20%E2%80%94%20in%20cities%20across%20the%20country%2C%20workers%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FAsvya%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Symbol%20map%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FAsvya%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20is%20looking%20to%20bring%20on%20a%20Robotaxi%20insurance%20claims%20specialist%20who%20will%20play%20%26quot%3Ba%20critical%20role%20in%20managing%20incident%20reporting%20and%20claim%20processes%20for%20Tesla%20Robotaxi%20and%20ride-hailing%20operations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20broad%20swath%20of%20locations%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20cities%20across%2010%20states%20%E2%80%94%20shows%20how%20intent%20Tesla%20and%20Musk%20are%20about%20scaling%20the%20service.%20Musk%20said%20in%20July%20that%20it%20would%20expand%20at%20%26quot%3Ba%20hyper-exponential%20rate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20we%20will%20probably%20have%20autonomous%20ride-hailing%20in%20probably%20half%20the%20population%20of%20the%20US%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20has%20repeatedly%20said%20Tesla's%20valuation%20is%20based%20on%20its%20ability%20to%20launch%20true%20self-driving%20technology%20at%20scale.%20Still%2C%20Tesla%20has%20long%20been%20seen%20as%20lagging%20behind%20competitors%20like%20Waymo%20and%20Zoox.%20Those%20companies'%20autonomous%20driving%20technology%20has%20been%20deployed%20in%20half%20a%20dozen%20cities%20across%20the%20country%2C%20some%20operating%20for%20several%20years%20already.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla's%20ride-hailing%20service%20has%20completed%20over%2040%2C000%20rides%20in%20California%20since%20July%2C%20according%20to%20the%20company.%20Waymo%2C%20by%20comparison%2C%20recorded%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwaymo-paid-rides-collision-increased-data-california-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E700%2C000%20rides%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20March%20alone%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20California%20Public%20Utilities%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20has%20said%20Tesla%20will%20be%20able%20to%20expand%20its%20service%20much%20quicker%20and%20at%20a%20lower%20cost%20using%20its%20vision-only%20system%2C%20which%20is%20trained%20on%20data%20from%20millions%20of%20Tesla%20owners%20and%20operates%20without%20expensive%20LiDAR%20and%20radar%20technology.%20For%20now%2C%20Musk%20said%2C%20the%20company%20will%20launch%20in%20many%20of%20the%20cities%20Waymo%20already%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20representative%20for%20Tesla%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Tesla's%20hiring%20shows%20the%20company%20is%20scaling%20up%2C%20some%20local%20authorities%20say%20the%20company%20has%20yet%20to%20take%20the%20steps%20for%20full%20deployment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20from%20the%20Nevada%20Department%20of%20Motor%20Vehicles%20and%20the%20Arizona%20Department%20of%20Transportation%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Tesla%20has%20received%20approval%20to%20test%20its%20service%20in%20the%20states%2C%20but%20still%20needs%20to%20complete%20additional%20steps%20to%20begin%20operating%20the%20vehicles%20commercially.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20representative%20for%20the%20city%20of%20Tampa%20said%20Tesla%20has%20not%20been%20in%20contact%20with%20the%20city%20regarding%20its%20plans%20to%20launch%20a%20Robotaxi%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20the%20other%20states%20and%20cities%20listed%20in%20job%20postings%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20has%20been%20sending%20test%20drivers%20to%20cities%20across%20the%20US%20as%20a%20part%20of%20an%20initiative%20internally%20referred%20to%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-self-driving-software-test-drivers-project-rodeo-experiences-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BProject%20Rodeo%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20far%20back%20as%202021%2C%20according%20to%20three%20former%20test%20drivers.%20The%20drivers%20train%20the%20autonomous%20software%20how%20to%20navigate%20roads%20in%20major%20cities%2C%20including%20New%20York%20City%2C%20Boston%2C%20Chicago%2C%20and%20Detroit%2C%20while%20also%20pushing%20the%20system%20to%20the%20limit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAhead%20of%20the%20Austin%20Robotaxi%20launch%20in%20June%2C%20the%20company%20had%20around%20300%20test%20drivers%20in%20the%20city%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-robotaxi-launch-austin-june-internal-details-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d696c969-8774-4198-a5f1-01b454337490%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERegulatory%20roadblocks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20far%20the%20biggest%20obstacle%20to%20Musk's%20robotaxi%20ambitions%20is%20the%20patchwork%20regulation%20for%20autonomous%20vehicles%20in%20the%20US.%20A%20lack%20of%20a%20federal%20framework%20has%20left%20regulating%20robotaxis%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20states%2C%20many%20of%20which%20have%20taken%20different