om%2C%20I%20find%20meal%20planning%20to%20often%20be%20a%20mental%20drain%2C%20especially%20when%20trying%20to%20cater%20to%20selective%20eater%2C%26quot%3B%20Ijeoma%20Nwaogu%2C%20a%20mother%20of%20three%2C%20wrote%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-parenting-meal-planning-family-schedule-mom-guilt-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eessay%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E.%20An%20example%20of%20a%20prompt%20she%20uses%20is%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20picky%20eaters%20that%20don't%20like%20spicy%20foods.%20Meal%20needs%20to%20be%20delicious%20for%20kids.%20I%20have%20chicken%2C%20rice%2C%20seasoning%2C%20oil.%20Create%20a%20recipe.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221594%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ijeoma%20Nwaogu%20and%20her%20family.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690cdc1d7f37aa653f55872a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221196%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIjeoma%20Nwaogu%20and%20her%20family.%3Cp%3EBlue%20Iguana%20Media%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Schmidt%20said%20she%20uses%20ChatGPT%20for%20to-do%20lists%20or%20meal-planning%20%E2%80%94%20running%20an%20inventory%20of%20everything%20she%20has%20at%20home%2C%20to%20generate%20lists%20of%20cheaper%20ingredient%20swaps%20or%20factor%20in%20discounts%20from%20a%20nearby%20grocery%20store%2C%20and%20to%20tweak%20existing%20recipes%20to%20accommodate%20every%20family%20member's%20dietary%20preferences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoorehead%20said%20these%20kinds%20of%20prompts%20are%20generally%20OK.%20She%20advised%20against%20asking%20ChatGPT%20to%20weigh%20in%20on%20a%20parenting%20scenario%2C%20because%20AI%20tools%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20very%20biased.%20She%20also%20recommended%20looking%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fperplexity-makes-200-ai-browser-free-to-battle-ai-slop-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20platforms%20like%20Perplexity%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20are%20known%20for%20citing%20their%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20AI%20is%20not%20a%20substitute%20for%20a%20real-life%20pediatrician%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-therapy-risks-benefits-boundaries-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emental%20health%20professional%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDe-identifying%20the%20kid%20or%20the%20school%20seems%20like%20a%20good%20safety%20practice%2C%20just%20as%20we're%20learning%20more%20about%20these%20models%2C%26quot%3B%20Moorehead%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20a%20good%20rule%20of%20thumb%20is%20never%20to%20include%20information%20that%20would%20make%20your%20child%20trackable%20if%20it%20appeared%20on%20another%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227a1c386b-6875-4947-9bec-0122951c8e66%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFreed%20up%20for%20more%20quality%20time%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20using%20ChatGPT%2C%20Nwaogu%20felt%20like%20she%20was%20being%20a%20good-enough%20mother.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20found%20myself%20trapped%20in%20a%20cycle%20of%20questioning%20whether%20I%20was%20doing%20things%20right%2C%20whether%20I%20was%20doing%20enough%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchmidt%20felt%20she%20couldn't%20give%20her%20kids%20as%20much%20attention%20as%20she%20wanted%20to.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20the%20kind%20of%20mom%20who%20wants%20to%20make%20their%20childhood%20feel%20magical%2C%20and%20that%20they%20remember%20me%20in%20a%20very%20positive%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20for%20the%20first%20three%20and%20a%20half%20years%2C%20I%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foverachieving-parent-burnout-learned-ask-help-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estuck%20in%20survival%20mode%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchmidt%20felt%20that%20instead%20of%20spending%20time%20with%20her%20daughter%2C%20her%20priority%20was%20managing%20th